Despite an acknowledgement that fluid overload can be associated with poor outcomes in critical care populations, the optimal clinical definition of fluid overload remains unclear [8]. In 2001, Goldstein et al. developed definitions for fluid overload that relied upon measuring fluid input and output from PICU admission [9]. This method for calculation of fluid overload is demonstrated below:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
